  array('post_name' => 'christian-cowan-a-fun-neon-collection','post_title' => 'Christian Cowan: A Fun Neon Collection','post_content' => 'Christian Cowan once again teams up with Giuseppe Zanotti to present the Fall\'19 Collection during the NYFW. This year the designer duo were inspired with the oversharing culture by influencers on social media. What came out of the "break the internet" theme was fun over the top collection in neon colors.

The collection was in continuity with his spring collection just with brighter shades and more options. It got a set of mix reactions from the audiences. A lot of day wear options were added this time. There were the trademark sweatshirts and the mini dresses were overlayed with rhinestones. The over jazzy neck pieces serves as straps for the gowns whereas wristwatches served as straps for the neon high heels. The collection was in sync with the theme, though there ere some pieces that failed to make the mark. But the question remains - how long can Christian Cowan continue along the same lines of pieces?

