  array('post_name' => 'chanel-metiers-dart-show-18-19-at-seoul','post_title' => 'Chanel takes the Métiers d’art Show\'18-\'19 to Seoul','post_content' => 'The Fashion House of Chanel presented its Métiers d’art Show second collection to Seoul on the 28th May 2019. The show was presented at the cultural hub of the famous S Factory in Seoul. The show was first available to the audience in the scenery of the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Temple_of_Dendur" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Temple of Dendour</a> in the Metropolitan Museum last year.

The collection is supposed to offer a modern and subtle take on the interpretations of Egypt\'s timeless palimpsest and the spirited streets of New York City. Graffiti prints and graphic lines were weaved in gold to mirror the skyscrapers of the city. The brand\'s in-house ambassador, Kristen Stewart, made an appearance for the event in Seoul. The show also saw A-list stars from Korea graced this event and some of them also walked down the runway for it. The show was followed by an exclusive after-party with live performances to celebrate the collection hitting the Chanel Stores.

