  array('post_name' => 'the-best-court-side-wimbledon-fashion-2019','post_title' => 'The Best Court-Side Wimbledon Fashion 2019','post_content' => 'Wimbledon is one of the oldest sports tournament in the world. Along with being such a prestigious tennis tournament, it is perhaps also the most glamorous one. While the players delight people with their on-court performances and try to win the coveted trophy over the span of two weeks, celebs visiting the matches desire to get in the best-dressed list of the tournament. Though it is no runway, Wimbledon Fashion is still no less than a Semi-formal red carpet affair. Wimbledon attracts tennis-watchers from all diverse fields and one shouldn\'t be surprised if they catch Hollywood elite, pop stars, royals, supermodels, designers and other sports, sports players mingling with one another especially during the finals weekend.

You know the Wimbledon fashion quotient is going to be high when Ralph Lauren is the \'Official Outfitter of The Championships,\' at the tournament for the 14th year. This means that the luxury brand designs and outfits all chair umpires, line umpires, ball persons and grounds people at Wimbledon during the tournament. They also dressed a lot of celebs gracing the event.

This year too various celebs descended the grounds of Wimbledon. The likes of Kate Middleton, Meghan Markle, Benedict Cumberbatch, Tom Hiddleston,  Pharrell Williams, Geri Horner, Anna Wintour, Sienna Miller, Ellie Goulding, David Beckham and many more were seen at Wimbledon. Some of the best dressed at  Wimbledon this year were:

[gallery columns="2" size="full" ids="21535,21536,21537,21538,21539,21540,21541,21542,21543,21544,21545,21546,21547,21548,21549,21550,21551,21552,21553,21554,21555,21556,21557,21558,21559,21560,21561,21562,21563,21564,21534,21565"]','post_excerpt' => '','post_date' => '2019-07-23 21:02:47'),
  array('post_name' => 'fall19-couture-alexandre-vauthier','post_title' => 'Fall\'19 Couture: Alexandre Vauthier','post_content' => '<blockquote>
<h4 style="text-align: center;"><em>“Couture, aussi pour le jour”</em></h4>
</blockquote>
With this and Paris as his vision in mind, Alexandre Vauthier\'s Fall\'19 Collection and the whole show could find hints and inspiration from the glamorous fashion city of the world, Paris. The soundtrack was from the eighties band, Taxi girl. The scent, a&nbsp;reminiscent of the tuberose scent created by&nbsp;Francis Kurkdjian. The&nbsp;silhouettes perfectly tailored, just as the French like it. In short the whole collection was a trip down the memory lane for Vauthier as he traced what made him want to be a designer. Backstage before the Fall\'19 runway show, the designer was quoted as saying:
<blockquote>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>“I wanted to reference the images, the silhouettes that seduced me as a child, everything that made me want to make fashion. Lesage, pleating, ruffles, there’s incredible work on the clothes. Couture is, in essence, this: the showcase for specialty skills that are quintessentially French, and Parisian.”</em></p>
</blockquote>
The Fall\'19 Collection was subtle, i.e. it was not over done in embellishments. The palette for the collection was black, white and pastel shades of sky pink and light blue. There was a bit of hand-painted floral work to give the collection a light, sweet and romantic vibe. There were boxed jackets and tailored pants giving it a touch of the 80\'s. Skirts ,ruffle front shirts, jersey and sultry dresses rounded up the collection.

[gallery size="full" ids="21601,21600,21599,21598,21597,21592,21593,21594,21595,21596,21587,21582,21583,21588,21589,21584,21585,21590,21591,21586,21577,21572,21573,21578,21579,21575,21580,21581,21576,21567,21568,21569,21570,21571"]

Pictures Courtesy of:&nbsp;Filippo Fior / Gorunway.com / Vogue.com

Also Read -&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ifashionnetwork.com/?p=21604&amp;preview=true&amp;preview_id=21604">Fall\'19 Couture: Chanel</a>

