  array('post_name' => 'fall19-couture-giambattista-valli','post_title' => 'Fall\'19 Couture: Giambattista Valli','post_content' => 'Giambattista Valli decided to ditch the runway this season and present his Fall\'19 Couture Collection in a museum-like setup. Giving a miss to the runway, the collection was spread across three rooms showcasing what the designer described as the art of the atelier followed by his obsessions. The designer released a capsule collection in collaboration with H&amp;M at the Cannes Film Festival in May bringing Haute Couture together with high street fashion.
<blockquote>
<h4 style="text-align: center;">“It’s extraordinary and unexpected. I never thought Giambattista Valli was so widely known and such an object of desire. In fact, we reached 600 million people through social media. It was a beautiful conversation.”</h4>
</blockquote>
<p style="text-align: left;">The showcasing took place at the Shangri-La hotel in Paris. The first room contained pieces depicting monogrammed white button-downs and tulle skirts. The next room showed bustier dresses and mini dresses. The designer used floral embroideries of orange blossoms, dahlias and roses in his pieces. The last room showed a balance of the work he had been doing with H&amp;M. It was the complete opposite of the pieces he had been doing with a high street brand. Frothy frilled gowns, sweeping trains and cape backs in pale mint, peachy orange, and light blue highlighted the room. “They balance each other out. It’s really a luxury to take the time to do things,” Valli said.</p>
&nbsp;

[gallery size="full" ids="21755,21765,21760,21764,21759,21754,21753,21758,21763,21762,21757,21752,21751,21756,21761,21746,21741,21736,21737,21742,21747,21748,21743,21738,21739,21744,21749,21750,21745,21740"]','post_excerpt' => '','post_date' => '2019-08-14 22:20:46'),
  array('post_name' => 'fall19-couture-alberta-ferretti-limited-edition','post_title' => 'Fall\'19 Couture: Alberta Ferretti Limited Edition','post_content' => 'Having said that, Alberta Ferretti the young Italian designer presented a collection 3-D embroideries, volumes and bold designs. The structures were more refined but there as a n underlying simplicity to the whole collection. The designer wanted to reflect “a woman’s strong identity,” through her Fall\'19 Couture Collection along with her appreciation for  “a dress that can move, accompany and transform a woman.”
<blockquote>
<h4 style="text-align: center;"><strong>“I like simplicity but not simplification.”</strong></h4>
</blockquote>
What was different and so unlike Ferretti in this collection was also the color palette she picked for her pieces. Mostly known for picking a palette of dustier and paler hues, Feretti picked bright and bold shades of chartruese, fire red, turquoise, and fuchsia for the Fall\'19 Couture Collection. Yet, one could see the trademarks of Ferretti with the elements of romance and magic as she added a touch of eccentricity in her pieces. One can get a whimsical feel in the aquamarine gown or the winged cape over the fitted pants. The designer has also tried to increase the day wear pieces as she adds a pair of pants with a top and a couple of dresses.

[gallery columns="2" size="full" ids="21817,21818,21819,21820,21821,21822,21823,21824,21825,21826,21827,21828,21829,21830,21831,21832,21833,21834,21835,21836"]

Pictures Courtesy of: Courtesy of Alberta Ferretti Limited Edition/ Vogue.com

Also Read - Fall\'19 Couture: Alexis Mabille','post_excerpt' => '','post_date' => '2019-08-27 22:05:58'),
  array('post_name' => 'fall19-couture-dundas','post_title' => 'Fall\'19 Couture: Dundas','post_content' => '<a href="https://www.instagram.com/peter_dundas/?hl=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Peter Dundas</a> set an 80\'s mood with his Fall\'19 Spring Collection. The designer described his Fall\'19 Collection as “Urban, funky, jungle chic.” The young brand presented a collection which was a fusion of couture with a bit of sporty feel. Other than that there were a lot of animal prints and the silhouettes were mostly short and sexy. The dresses had a lot of beadwork, sequins, metallic lamé, and leather fringe. The color palette was dominated by gold and animal print shades with the occasional hot pink and mustard popping up here and there. The footwears were mostly animal printed strappy sandals and were a bit of a miss. The Collection showed promise but there are still ways to go for the brand. The designer will also present his first men\'s collection this season.

[gallery size="full" ids="21773,21774,21775,21776,21777,21778,21779,21780,21782,21783,21784,21785,21786,21787,21788,21789,21790,21791,21792,21793,21794,21795,21796,21797,21798,21799,21800,21801,21802,21803,21804,21805,21806,21807,21808,21809,21810,21811,21812,21813,21814,21815"]

Picture Credits: Kim WestonArnold / Indigital.tv

Also read: Fall\'19 Couture: Alberta Ferretti','post_excerpt' => '','post_date' => '2019-08-27 22:10:43'),
  array('post_name' => 'fall19-couture-alexis-mabille','post_title' => 'Fall\'19 Couture: Alexis Mabille','post_content' => 'Alexis Mabille titled his Fall\'19 Couture Collection  Tête-à-Tête as he went back to the basics of couture. “I wanted to get back to the very essence of couture, which is about a personal relationship between the designer and the client,” Mabille explained. Couture, back in the day was never about ready-to-wear pieces, but about customizing an outfit according to the fancies of a particular client. The designer used the glided salon of 19th Century mansion\'s Fondation Dosne-Thiers in Paris instead of the runway.

Alexis Mabille had no particular silhouette in mind while creating his Fall\'19 Collection. Instead, he used his vast clientele as an inspiration to play with the contrasts of minimalist - maximal and introvert-extrovert. The diverse collection was just that - diverse, in every sense possible. Every piece had a different shape and silhouette. One could find sleek pieces along with bustier pieces, there were capes trailing corsets and dresses. There was a wrap dress alongside a collared blouse with a pleated skirt. One could find elements of elegance, romance, grand gestures along with a little bit of wit in Alexis Mabille\'s Fall\'19 Collection. It was a joyful collection indeed!

[gallery size="full" columns="2" ids="21839,21840,21841,21842,21843,21844,21845,21846,21847,21848,21849,21850,21851,21852,21853,21854,21855"]

Pictures Courtesy of:  Alexis Mabille/ Vogue.com

Also Read - Fall\'19 Couture: Antonio Grimaldi','post_excerpt' => '','post_date' => '2019-08-28 22:43:01'),
  array('post_name' => 'venice-film-festival-red-carpet-day-1','post_title' => 'Venice Film Festival: Red Carpet Day 1','post_content' => 'The oldest Film Festival is back with a bang! The 76th Venice Film Festival is taking place in Venice from August 28 to September 7. Inaugurated in 1932, The Venice Film Festival is part of the three big film festivals along with Cannes Film Festival and Berlin Film Festival. The festival is all set with a line up of impressive screenings and not to forget the glamorous fashion celebrities from around the world bring here. This year The Truth (La Vérité) starring actresses Catherine Deneuve and Juliette Binoche open the festival.  As the festival began, people were treated to a fine display of fashion and couture. Here are some of the best looks from the opening day from the Venice film festival:

<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-21858" src="https://www.ifashionnetwork.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/gettyimages-1170736768.jpg" alt="Venice Film Festival" width="980" height="1475" />

Juliette Binoche in  Armani Privé and Catherine Deneuve in Jean Paul Gaultier Haute Couture during the "La Vérité" (The Truth) Premiere &amp; Opening Ceremony

<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-21859" src="https://www.ifashionnetwork.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/hbz-venice-film-festival-elsa-hosk-gettyimages-1170740945.jpg" alt="Venice Film Festival" width="980" height="1470" />

Elsa Hosk in Etro during "La Vérité" (The Truth) Premiere &amp; Opening Ceremony

