  array('post_name' => 'a-humming-way-spring-summer-20-collection-met-with-warmth-and-excitement-during-caafd-nyfw','post_title' => 'A Humming Way Spring/Summer 20 Collection Met with Warmth and Excitement During CAAFD NYFW','post_content' => 'A Humming Way is an Indian brand inspired by the old world regalia of the state of Rajasthan in India. With the support of CAAFD, this was the first time that the designer brand was showcasing their collection at the New York Fashion Week. The collection was titled "Matsutake," and represented the mushroom\'s characteristics of adaptability with utmost brilliance. Matsutake is also known to spread a feeling of hope and that is what Sweta Agarwal tried to emit through her showcasing.

The collection had 14 pieces in total. It had a mix of cocktail dresses, gowns and jumpsuits all in a palette of soft pink, browns, greys and white. The collection had a lot of mirrors work to trace the roots from which the designer label began. A humming Way\'s entire collection was soothing and quite welcoming.

[gallery columns="2" size="full" ids="22200,22201,22202,22203,22204,22205,22206,22207,22208,22209,22210,22211,22212,22213"]

