  array('post_name' => 'spring-summer-2020-collection-nyfw-afffair','post_title' => 'Spring/Summer 2020 Collection at the NYFW: Afffair','post_content' => 'Azerbajiani designer, Rufat Ismayil opened the New York Fashion Week as he showcased his brand Afffair\'s Spring/Summer 2020 Collection at his Spring Studios. The collection was inspired by Ismayil\'s homeland, \'Azerajiani.\' The designer set the mood with the Middle Eastern remix music which was played while the model walked the runway.

Think of this brand and the first thing that comes to mind are evening gowns in contemporary and sophisticated designs and it was the same for this season. The collection was titled, "<em><strong>KHARI BULBUL</strong></em>" and with the tagline, "<em><strong>When Fashion meets Perfection.</strong></em>" The Spring/Summer 2020 was vibrant in every way from it\'s color palette to the diverse designs of evening gowns. In picking a palette the designer  picked a range that was spread across light heather blues and pastel pinks to purples and tangerines. The whole collection was dominated by fringes and ruffles. Other than that, the designer also used organza, chiffon and silk in his gowns. The designer showed constraint in his collection because even though the materials used were heavy, the gowns never crossed the line and became too much to handle.  A beautiful, fun collection to start the New York Fashion Week.

[gallery columns="2" size="full" ids="22274,22275,22276,22277,22278,22279,22280,22281,22282,22283,22284,22285,22286,22287,22288,22289,22290,22291,22292,22293,22294,22295,22296,22297,22298,22303,22299,22300,22301,22302"]

Pictures Courtesy of: VRAI Magazine','post_excerpt' => '','post_date' => '2019-09-24 07:57:35'),
  array('post_name' => 'spring-summer-2020-collection-at-nyfw-cong-tri','post_title' => 'Spring/Summer 2020 Collection at NYFW: Cong Tri','post_content' => 'The designer label Cong Tri recently came into limelight when Beyoncé wore the brand for the premier of Lion King earlier this year. Now, the Vietnamese label has presented it\'s Spring/Summer 2020 Collection at the New York Fashion Week.  The collection at 60 pieces looked elegant and effortless not to mention refreshing. There was a balance in the pieces. One could not call it minimalist or over the top.

The pieces mostly had simple silhouettes and the collection mostly consisted of A-line gowns and sleek cocktail dresses. The designer also threw in some pants and jumpsuits along with a bit of swimwear. The trains were simple and graceful. Creative Director, Nguyen Cong Tri picked a palette which was as colorful as the season of Spring. The colors of the rainbow were on display individually in the dresses and also in his finale piece, the rainbow dress. Cong Tri\'s beautiful short dress which was made of rainbow-colored feathers impressed us not to mention steal the show as well.

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

[gallery columns="6" size="full" ids="22560,22561,22562,22563,22564,22565,22566,22567,22568,22569,22570,22571,22572,22573,22574,22575,22576,22577,22578,22579,22580,22581,22582,22583,22584,22585,22586,22587,22588,22589,22590,22591,22592,22593,22594,22595,22596,22597,22598,22599,22600,22601,22602,22603,22604,22605,22606,22607,22608,22609,22610,22611,22612,22613,22614,22615,22616,22617,22618,22619"]

