  array('post_name' => 'spring-summer-2020-collection-at-nyfw-helmut-lang','post_title' => 'Spring/Summer 2020 Collection at NYFW: Helmut Lang','post_content' => 'A white industrial space and the soundtrack of electronic beats is what welcome the audience at Helmut Lang\'s Spring/Summer 2020 Collection at the New York Fashion Week. Mark Thomas, creative director for men’s and women’s, and Thomas Cawson, creative director for jeans, put up a collection that was minimalist yet not boring.

The designer duo picked up and evolved a little from where they had left the collection last season. The collection aimed at refining the era of the 90\'s. The tailoring was impeccable. The outfits were well color-coordinated (mostly monochromatic). The silhouettes were sleek and simple. The addition of utilitarian parkas, the chromed leather and the various experiments with denim shapes gave the collection a modern touch. Overall, Mark Thomas and Thomas Cawson stayed true to the label\'s originality with their deconstructed aesthetics.

[gallery columns="6" size="full" ids="22740,22739,22741,22742,22743,22744,22745,22746,22747,22748,22749,22750,22751,22752,22753,22754,22755,22756,22757,22758,22759,22760,22761,22762,22763,22764,22765,22766,22767,22768,22769,22770,22771,22772,22773,22774,22775,22776,22777,22778,22779"]

Pictures Courtesy of:  Filippo Fior / Gorunway.com/ Vogue.com

