  array('post_name' => 'self-portrait-spring-summer-2020-collection','post_title' => 'Self-Portrait: Spring/Summer 2020 Collection','post_content' => 'Designer Han Chong presented the Spring/Summer 2020 Collection for Self-Portrait at Woolworth Building in New York during the NYFW. The collection captured the essence of Spring as it was breezy and romantic. Other than that, the collection was also urban chic and comfortable. Coming from the brand of Self-Portrait, this was quite fresh and different compared to their usually famous wedding dresses.

Han Chong\'s palette selection was all summery with the pastel hues of blue, lilac and pale yellow with the exception of hot pink and vivid-orange red thrown in the mix. The opening piece was a cotton poplin with lace trim and ruffled sleeves. The dresses had an ease to it as they came mostly in looser silhouettes. Day-wear dominated the collection with good options of frocks, shirt-dresses, and long flowing dress. The long hats added a nice touch. One may not find this season\'s Self-Portrait pieces on the red carpet of movie premiers but easily during a day out for lunch or at a family wedding.

