  array('post_name' => 'frank-ocean-is-the-new-face-of-prada','post_title' => 'Frank Ocean is the new face of Prada','post_content' => 'Frank Ocean is the new face of Prada in its new SS20 campaign. Frank Ocean who is an American singer-songwriter, photographer and record producer, has been announced the new face of Prada in its SS20 campaign that has been labeled "Optimist Rhythm”. Frank Ocean has always been a huge fan of Prada and has often been seen sporting it at various events such as the Met Gala 2019 and on the cover of W magazine.

[caption id="attachment_26985" align="alignnone" width="940"]<img class="wp-image-26985 size-full" src="https://ifashionnetwork.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Screen-Shot-2020-01-12-at-2.49.43-PM.png" alt="" width="940" height="1166"> Source: Prada[/caption]

Fans are surprised to see Frank as the new face of Prada since he\'s known to keep a low profile and is rarely seen giving interviews or photoshoots. So to see him lead an entire fashion campaign is a surprise to most. However,&nbsp;this is not his first time modeling as he has already appeared in campaigns for Calvin Klein and Band of Outsiders.

The photographs for the campaign have been captured by photographer David Sims in both black and white as well as color. One image sees Ocean in a parquet-floored apartment donning a long coat, an oversized shirt, a pair of cropped camel trousers, and a slim bolo tie much similar to the look he wore to the Met Gala in 2019.

In another image, we see him in a black roll-neck sweater staring off into the distance as if caught in the moment.

Frank Ocean, the new face of Prada, has also put his own words into Prada\'s acronym and the Prada logo has been repurposed for the season. The Prada logo now reads “Programming Rhythms And Dancing Again” that has been derived from \'abstract ideas, thoughts and notions\' as described by the press release issued by the label.

Actor Austin Butler, as well as director Nicolas Winding Refn, are also the faces for this season of Prada\'s new campaign and they look great as well.

The year 2020 is going great for Frank Ocean who has recently been announced to headline Coachella this year. We last heard from Ocean in 2016 of his album Blonded, and it only seems fair to say he\'s making a major comeback this year after a hiatus of 4 years.

&nbsp;','post_excerpt' => '','post_date' => '2020-01-13 16:21:48'),
  array('post_name' => 'classic-blue-the-color-for-2020','post_title' => 'Classic Blue: The Color for 2020','post_content' => 'Paint company Pantone has declared its color for the year 2020: Classic Blue. To be specific, PANTONE 19-4052 Classic Blue according to the company parlance. Pantone is the reigning authority when it comes to forecasting colors over the past two decades. Pantone’s Color of the Year has influenced product development and purchasing decisions in multiple industries, including fashion, home furnishings, and industrial design, as well as product packaging and graphic design. For the year 2019, Pantone picked living coral to be the color of the year.

<img class="wp-image-26992 aligncenter" src="https://ifashionnetwork.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/pantone-colour-of-the-year-2020-classic-blue-design_dezeen_2364_sq.jpg" alt="" width="595" height="595" />

“Instilling calm, confidence, and connection, this enduring blue hue highlights our desire for a dependable and stable foundation on which to build as we cross the threshold into a new era,” says Pantone, in the color profile accompanying the announcement. “Imprinted in our psyches as a restful color, PANTONE 19-4052 Classic Blue brings a sense of peace and tranquility to the human spirit, offering refuge. Aiding concentration and bringing laser-like clarity, Pantone 19-4052 Classic Blue re-centers our thoughts. A reflective blue tone, Classic Blue fosters resilience.”

In her statement,  Leatrice Eiseman, the executive director Pantone Color Institute said,  “We are living in a time that requires trust and faith. It is this kind of constancy and confidence that is expressed by Pantone 19-4052 Classic Blue. It is a solid and dependable blue hue we can always rely on. Imbued with a deep resonance, Pantone 19-4052 Classic Blue provides an anchoring foundation. A boundless blue evocative of the vast and infinite evening sky, Pantone 19-4052 Classic Blue encourages us to look beyond the obvious to expand our thinking; challenging us to think more deeply, increase our perspective and open the flow of communication," she added.

<img class="wp-image-26993 aligncenter" title="Classic Blue" src="https://ifashionnetwork.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/pantone-colour-of-the-year-2020-classic-blue-design_dezeen_2364_col_15-852x637-1.jpg" alt="" width="646" height="483" />

The selection process for a color stars well a year in advance of the announcement. The process requires thoughtful consideration and trend analysis. Pantone’s color experts at the Pantone Color Institute comb the world looking for new color influences for the selection of color. This includes the entertainment industry, traveling art collections and new artists, fashion, all areas of design, popular travel destinations, as well as new lifestyles, playstyles, and socio-economic conditions. Influences may also stem from new technologies, materials, textures, and effects that impact color, relevant social media platforms and even upcoming sporting events that capture worldwide attention.

Also Read - <a href="https://ifashionnetwork.com/?p=26953&amp;preview=true">Rami Malek: The new face of YSL</a>','post_excerpt' => '','post_date' => '2020-01-14 21:33:45'),
  array('post_name' => 'tom-ford-fashion-week-fall-2020','post_title' => 'Tom Ford Fashion week Fall 2020 (Ready-To-wear)','post_content' => 'Tom ford gives us some major runs for the Oscar red carpet Friday night when he shows cast has an amazing full 2020 collection. Many well-known faces like Renee Zellweger, Catherine O’Hara, Kate Hudson, Bryan Lou Red, Anna Wintour giggling with Jeff Bezos—the full pack of celebrity list went on and on. They all were present off the runway, admiring the spectacular collection by Tom ford on NY fashion week. Gigi, Bella Hadid, and Kendall Jenner were seen walking the runway with some innovative design, which they pulled off like a real star. His collection with a surprisingly focused on everyday look rather than red carpet designs. He went with something quite inspiring and easy going. He has, in fact, an eye-catching and tremendous perspective that the fashion industry desperately needs. His new designs are emphatically distinct and manifest. He puts so much creativity in every single design he creates.
<h5>-Oversized sweater collection Along with skirts</h5>
The collection consisted of oversized sweaters paired with a hip-hugging skirt and feathery golden dipped earrings. Undoubtedly, he has proven himself again with his creative mind. The models were, moreover, seen wearing socks with high edgy heels, which looked fantastic.

He pop-up more color combinations with black. Black half torn sleeves sweeter combined with multi-patterned skirt and green printed long heel boots.
<h5>-Pants and jacket, Collection</h5>
He pursues his amazing collection with Wide leg pants shrunken jacket, which made glamour more see-through. Without a second thought, track pants were correctly worn with tie-dye caftan cap and gold-dipped earrings. Over and above, he went with The magnificent oversized shearling cheetah printed jackets twin with check pants and track pants. Cheetah baggy pants were also paired up with all black with looked outstanding. Long coats were also part of his magnificent collection.
<h5>-Velvet, the new trend</h5>
Vivid violet and electric blue suit with wide-lapel hourglass over hip-hugging skirt were vibrant yet very classy. Withal, turtleneck styled sweater over a sequin tulle skirt which brings the pure classic color of American style. We have seen different colored shimmery sequin bling design skirts put together with back sweaters.

Fort winds up his runway with evening looks, with some dramatic disco lights that add more life, some drama, and fun to the show. Gigi was caught wearing a black undershirt topped with a black shearling blazer. Jeans\' textured skirt looked sizzling hot with black high boots. I feel the collection was Tom ford, one of the best recent collections with was pulled off beautifully. You can see yourself wearing this collection for daily looks. At the same time, we can also see the amount of effort he put in his work and how everything turned out.

-Photos Credit: Alessandro Lucioni/Gorunway.com

[gallery size="full" columns="4" ids="27156,27157,27158,27159,27160,27161,27162,27163,27164,27165,27166,27167,27168,27169,27170,27171,27172,27173,27174,27175,27176,27177,27178,27179,27180" link="file"]','post_excerpt' => '','post_date' => '2020-02-29 20:17:22'),
  array('post_name' => 'jason-wu-collection-fall-2020-collection','post_title' => 'Jason Wu Collection: Fall 2020 Collection','post_content' => '<span style="font-weight: 400;">On several occasions, the simplest of words are needed to describe something. Jason Wu Collection Fall 2020 was just that. It was beautiful and romantic. Designer Jason Wu’s inspiration for the Fall 2020 Collection was </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Orchids and Egon Schiele. Everything from the ambiance and runway to the collection was in sync with the theme.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;"> Jason Wu collaborated with Australian expressionist artist Jessica May Underwood this season. She is known for her erotic, and deeply psychological paintings, and her graphic orchid patterns were reproduced by Jason Wu on his pieces. The designer this season worked with a color palette of violet, teal, turquoise, and fuchsia. The whole focus of the collection was on craftsmanship and a play with the fabric.</span>
<h4 style="text-align: center;"><strong>“With this collection I really wanted to showcase New York’s craftsmanship because we don’t get credit for it.” </strong></h4>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">The opening piece was a hyper cape which set the tone for the evening. The Swarovski crystal work on the tulle dress was refined and elegant. Similarly, the play with feathers on the part frock made for a sophisticated piece. The pieces were timeless and crafted with perfection. The whole collection just went on to show the fineness and experience that the designer Jason Wu possesses after a decade and a half in the fashion industry.</span>

